README.md
     1â†’# python-dotenv
     3â†’[![Build Status][build_status_badge]][build_status_link]
     4â†’[![PyPI version][pypi_badge]][pypi_link]
     5â†’
     6â†’python-dotenv reads key-value pairs from a `.env` file and can set them as
     7â†’environment variables. It helps in the development of applications following the
     8â†’[12-factor](https://12factor.net/) principles.
     9â†’
    10â†’- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
    11â†’- [Other Use Cases](#other-use-cases)
    12â†’  - [Load configuration without altering the environment](#load-configuration-without-altering-the-environment)
    13â†’  - [Parse configuration as a stream](#parse-configuration-as-a-stream)
    14â†’  - [Load .env files in IPython](#load-env-files-in-ipython)
    15â†’- [Command-line Interface](#command-line-interface)
